records.nl_statement: Prove that $\frac{(x+2)^p-2^p}{x}$, where $p$ is an odd prime, is irreducible in $\mathbb{Z}[x]$.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Fintype Subgroup Set Polynomial Ideal
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_9_4_2d {p : ℕ} (hp : p.Prime ∧ p > 2)
  {f : Polynomial ℤ} (hf : f = (X + 2)^p):
  Irreducible (∑ n in (f.support \ {0}), (f.coeff n : Polynomial ℤ) * X ^ (n-1) :
  Polynomial ℤ) :=
